Doctor explained in detail about muscle mechanism of foot & compared both feet's strength. 
He rightly referred for Bone Density, calcium & other tests to understand the root cause & recommended accordingly medicines & diet planning.
He explained the risks of not taking the necessary steps in time.

review_reply.reply_text:
I don’t give unnecessary plaster and splint when it is not required
You have minor sprain with good movement of the thumb it will get better with time
Often vitamin deficiency delays the healing process
My consultation charges are same as per advertised on the site

survey_response.review_text: Doctor Hemant was very friendly. I felt Consultation charge of Rs.2000 for only 3 minutes, was high as the problem was just a thumb pain, nothing  complicated or serious. Besides, even the prescription was a pain killer (which I did not need) plus Uprise D3 which I am already taking,  except that I now had to take it more frequently.  But there was no immediate treatment for the thumb problem.

Oh !  he is so comforting and frank , so don’t Think of an option you have to do it or not it’s your opinion But he lays-the facts very clearly in front of you 
A friendly dr is very iHelpful because you can easily share your problems with him as he gives you all the time.
Go for him!!!!

Dr Bhandari was recommended to me by a close friend of mine and I’m so glad to have got operated by him. He is very friendly, down to earth and extremely approachable. Even though he is very busy and is one of the best at what he does, he cares about each and every patient of his personally.

** ****** **** ************* ** *** *********** ******** *** ********** * ************* * ******* ****** Suggests required to d point tests and treatment.

God Bless him

Dr. Bhandari gave me good suggestions and medecinal advice. I have gone through left arm humerus fracture surgery with a steel plate in Jan 2017. The union of bones have not fully developing. Dr. Bhandari has given suggestions for injection of gemtide which can help me avoid another surgery.

I have been to Doctor Bhandari a couple of times now, most recently for pain in my Neck / shoulder region after a fall while playing. I have had a great experience with the consultations. He is patient, hears you out, asks you questions which make things clearer for you, does a complete physical examination, recognises what could the issues be, explains them to you and recommends the necessary steps to rectify and correct the ongoing issue. Advises tests / x-rays / mri's if needed/not needed. 

Been to 3/4 other orthopaedics over the last decade, by far my experience with Dr. Hemant Bhandari has been the best.
Good and friendly Doctor...experienced doctor...good advice and suggestions...neat and clean clinic also
Dr Hemant Bhandhari Sir is excellent doctor and also good humain being.He explain very politly and in the language as the patients understand.

We know Sir,since 2006 when my mother was under his treatment at Bombay Hospital. He is a great doctor and a very nice human being. Thank you,Sir for taking good care of my mother. GOD bless you and your family.
